claim.claim-text:
1. A patch clamp chip for electrophysiology comprising:
a homogenous substrate selected from a group consisting of glass and quartz having a first outer surface and an opposing second outer surface;
a crater extending into one of the first and second outer surfaces and defining a crater diameter thereon; and
a pore extending between the crater and the other one of the first and second outer surfaces of the substrate, the pore defining a pore diameter that is smaller than the crater diameter and is generally constant along substantially the entire length of the pore, and wherein the length of the pore extends over a majority of a distance between the first outer surface and the opposing second outer surface of the substrate;
wherein at least one of the crater and the pore have a surface adapted to provide a gigaseal with respect to a cell membrane placed thereover.

5. A patch clamp chip for electrophysiology comprising:
a substrate having a first outer surface and an opposing second outer surface;
a crater extending into one of the first and second outer surfaces and defining a crater diameter thereon; and
a pore extending between the crater and the other one of the first and second outer surfaces of the substrate, the pore defining a pore diameter that is smaller than the crater diameter and is generally constant along a major portion of a length of the pore;
wherein the crater includes (i) a bottom wall, (ii) a sidewall extending outwardly away from the bottom wall, and (iii) an undercut that extends into the sidewall so as to define a sidewall shoulder between the undercut and the sidewall.

7. A patch clamp chip for electrophysiology comprising:
a homogenous substrate selected from a group consisting of glass and quartz having a first outer surface and an opposing second outer surface;
a crater defined by a sidewall having opposing facing surfaces and the sidewall defining a depth of the crater, the crater extending into one of the first and second outer surfaces and defining a crater diameter thereon defined by a greatest distance between the facing surfaces of the sidewall; and
a pore extending between the crater diameter and the other one of the first and second outer surfaces of the substrate, the pore defining a pore diameter that is smaller than the crater diameter and is generally constant along substantially the entire length of the pore;
wherein the pore further comprises (i) a pore-crater opening defining a pore-crater opening diameter defined at a location where the pore opens into the crater, and (ii) a pore-surface opening defining a pore-surface opening diameter defined at a location where the pore opens through an outer surface of the substrate material, and wherein the larger of the pore-crater and pore-surface opening diameters is no more than about 50% greater than the smaller of the pore-crater and pore-surface opening diameters;
wherein at least one of the crater and the pore are adapted to provide a gigaseal with respect to a cell membrane placed thereover.
